


# VSCO 

Nature of services: Mixed ‚Äî primarily public-facing (B2C) with critical internal services.
VSCO is a consumer photo/editing platform, so the user-facing apps and media APIs are public internet-facing; backend tooling, analytics, and admin dashboards are internal.

Key public-facing components

* Mobile & Web Frontend APIs ‚Äî handle user auth, profiles, feed, image upload/download, edits, filters.
* Media Processing & CDN ‚Äî image transcoding, resizing, format conversion; cached on CDN for global delivery.
* Authentication & Session Services ‚Äî OAuth/JWT issuing, refresh tokens.
* Search & Recommendations APIs ‚Äî user content discovery (high read traffic).
* Payment/subscription gateway ‚Äî if monetized (in-app purchases, subscriptions).

Key internal components

* Content moderation & admin dashboards ‚Äî tools for trust & safety teams.
* Analytics pipelines ‚Äî event collection, batch/stream processing (engagement metrics).
* Developer & CI/CD tooling ‚Äî build systems, staging environments, feature-flagging.
* Internal microservices ‚Äî ingestion pipelines, batch workers, ETL jobs.

Security & access patterns

* Public APIs protected via HTTPS, rate-limiting, WAF, token-based auth; CDNs offload static content.
* Internal services protected in private networks/VPCs, accessed via VPN/IDP-SAML SSO, and RBAC.
* Data privacy: user PII and media require encryption at rest and in transit; compliance with privacy laws (e.g., GDPR) depending on regions.

Operational considerations (what you‚Äôd manage)

* Scalability: autoscaling for upload/serve traffic; cache tuning and CDN rules to reduce origin load.
* Availability: multi-region deployments, active-active or active-passive for critical APIs, health checks, failover.
* Storage: object storage lifecycle policies, hot/cold tiers for old images, retention.
* Performance: CDN configuration, image optimization, latency budgets for page/app load.
* Monitoring & SLOs: API latency, error rate, media pipeline throughput, CDN cache hit ratio, storage usage.
* Incident types: CDN misconfig, origin overload, transcoder backlogs, authentication failures, data corruption.

Typical troubleshooting tasks

* SSH into app/media servers for logs; inspect queues, disk IO, CPU; check CDN edge error logs and origin latency; analyze application traces for slow requests; verify database/storage connectivity and performance.

Interview-ready short answer (VSCO)

> ‚ÄúFor a VSCO-like platform most services are public-facing (user apps, media APIs, CDN) and I also manage internal services (moderation tools, analytics, CI). My focus is on low-latency media delivery, CDN/cache tuning, autoscaling for spikes, secure auth, and ensuring storage and processing pipelines are reliable.‚Äù

